HEADWORD: Yardland
<hw>Yard"land`</hw> <pr>(y⟦aum⟧rd"l⟦acr⟧nd`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A measure of land of uncertain quantity,
varying from fifteen to forty acres; a virgate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

